### Get config
# Static defaults and limits enforced by the API -- fetch this before showing the create-poll form so
# the frontend never hardcodes values that could drift from actual server-side validation.
# maxPollDateRangeDays is the exact max offset (in days, inclusive) from today a poll date may be --
# POST /sessions enforces this identical value, so a frontend date-picker bounded by it should rarely
# offer a date the server rejects. "Today" is still resolved server-side, in the poll's timezone, at
# submit time -- a browser in a different timezone or a fetch/submit gap crossing a day boundary can
# still shift the edge by a day, so POST /sessions remains the authority and its 400 must still be
# handled.

GET {{host}}/config

# Response 200:
# {
#   "maxPollDates": 90,
#   "pollNameMaxLength": 100,
#   "participantNameMaxLength": 50,
#   "allowedSlotMinutes": [15, 30, 60, 90, 120],
#   "defaultSlotMinutes": 60,
#   "startEndMinuteStep": 15,
#   "maxPollDateRangeDays": 365,
#   "maxPollOverrideGroups": 10,
#   "maxUsersPerSession": 20,
#   "sessionExpireHours": 336
# }

###

### Create a poll
# Authenticated variant: POST {{host}}/sessions/authed (Cognito JWT via Authorization header).
# x-recaptcha-token is required only on the unauthenticated variant. The authed route (Cognito JWT)
# skips the reCAPTCHA check entirely — proving identity via a signed Google JWT replaces it.
#
# dates is a flat, sorted list of candidate ISO dates -- however the client generated them (a weekday-
# recurrence helper, or hand-picked individual dates), the API only ever sees the resolved list. Max
# length is MAX_POLL_DATES. Every date must be today or later, and at most maxPollDateRangeDays (see
# GET /config) days from today -- both checked against the poll's timezone.
#
# usesTimes toggles whether a time-of-day window applies:
# - false: no startMinute/endMinute/slotMinutes -- availability is one boolean per date.
# - true: startMinute/endMinute (minutes since local midnight, multiples of 15) define the window, and
#   slotMinutes (one of 15/30/60/90/120, default 60) is the length of each candidate meeting slot. Slot
#   start times slide across the window stepped by 30 minutes (15 minutes only when slotMinutes is 15) --
#   slots overlap rather than partition the range.
#
# overrides (optional, usesTimes: true only) lets specific dates use a different startMinute/endMinute
# than the poll's default window -- e.g. a shorter window on weekends. Each entry is a non-empty subset
# of this poll's own dates plus its own startMinute/endMinute (same validation rules as the top-level
# fields); slotMinutes is not overridable, it's always the one poll-level value. A date not covered by
# any override uses the poll's default window. No date may appear in more than one override group, and
# at most maxPollOverrideGroups (see GET /config) groups are allowed.

POST {{host}}/sessions
Content-Type: application/json
x-recaptcha-token: test-token

{
  "name": "Fall rec soccer practice",
  "dates": ["2025-09-04", "2025-09-05", "2025-09-06"],
  "usesTimes": true,
  "startMinute": 960,
  "endMinute": 1080,
  "slotMinutes": 60,
  "overrides": [{ "dates": ["2025-09-06"], "startMinute": 600, "endMinute": 840 }],
  "timezone": "America/Chicago"
}

# Response 201:
# { "sessionId": "spring-owl" }
#
# Response 400: missing name, empty/oversized/duplicate dates, invalid usesTimes combination, etc.
# Response 403: reCAPTCHA score too low (unauthenticated variant only)

###

### Get poll by ID
# slots is the server-generated Slot[][] for this poll (one slot array per date, in the same order as
# `dates`, from the same buildSlots output used internally for the overlap grid) -- the frontend renders
# grid/results columns from slots[dateIndex] instead of reimplementing slot generation. A date covered by
# an overrides group uses that group's window; every other date uses the poll's default window. Always a
# single 0-1440 slot per date for usesTimes: false polls.
GET {{host}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}

# Response 200:
# {
#   "sessionId": "spring-owl",
#   "name": "Fall rec soccer practice",
#   "dates": ["2025-09-04", "2025-09-05", "2025-09-06"],
